Interface IFastDecodableMessage

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IFIXMessage
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDepthFullUpdateMessage, AbstractMarketDataMessage, CSMAMessage, CSMDMessage, CSMHMessage, DepthDecoratorBase, DepthEntryIncrementalDecorator, DepthFullUpdateDecorator, DepthFullUpdateIncrementalDecorator, DepthFullUpdateSnapshotDecorator, ECNIMessage, ECNPMessage, EMXMessage, FIXMessageAsArray, FIXMessageAsIndexedByteArray, FIXMessageAsIndexedList, FIXMessageAsList, FIXMessageDecoratorBase, FIXMessageWithPluggableStore, MACKMessage, MarketDataDecoratorBase, MERRMessage, OINPMessage, OrderedFIXMessage, ReusableDepthEntryUpdateMessage, ReusableDepthFullUpdateMessage, ReusableDepthSnapshotMessage, ReusableMarketDataIncrementalRefresh, ReusableMarketDataTopOfBookSnapshot, ReusableMarketDataTopOfBookUpdate, ReusableMessage, RuleTrackingFIXMessage, SampleFastCompatibleMessage, SampleFIXMessage, ScpOutboundMessage, SetValueStoreMessage, TBKDMessage, TopOfBookIncrementalDecorator, TopOfBookSnapshotDecorator, TREQMessage, TRESMessage, VREQMessage, VRESMessage

    public interface IFastDecodableMessage
    This is the interface that message objects must implement so that this FAST implementation can decode a FAST input stream to the message.

    A message is assumed to be an ordered list of tags and associated values.

    See Also:
    IFastEncodableMessage

    • Method Detail

      • addField

        void addField(ITagValue value)
        Add a field with the given tag and value to the end of the list of message fields.
        Parameters:
        value - tag/value of field to add.

      • clearTagValues

        void clearTagValues()
        Clears out any existing message content - leaving an empty message, ie a message with no fields.

        Note that a message implementation that supports reuse may move the existing fields into a free pool for future reuse - for example, through the getFreeTagValue() method.

      • getFreeTagValue

        ITagValue getFreeTagValue()
        Returns a free tag value object, creating one if necessary.

        This is a better way of getting ITagValue objects than creating them yourself using new. This method allows tag value field reuse in reused messages.

        Returns:
        ITagValue object
